(88, '0', 'Here are some tips for reducing household electricity consumption and pay less (2023)', '', 'electrical', '<p><wt-ignore uuid=\"359f1d04-38f2-4c7f-8c20-8e9789844c4e\" source=\"wt-feature-result\" data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\">There\'s a surge in electricity prices in our country</wt-ignore><wt-ignore uuid=\"0b78bf06-4dcb-4d9f-8dc0-afcc72b2ebca\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">. </wt-ignore> <wt-ignore uuid=\"7dffbaa1-8a9f-48a1-8096-0deb1dd44172\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">To streamline our consumption, we have to take a few things into consideration</wt-ignore> .</p><p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">Electricity is a valuable resource that powers our daily lives. However, it is important to be mindful of our energy consumption in order to reduce our impact on the environment and save money on our electricity bills. By making a few simple changes and adopting energy-efficient habits, you can significantly reduce your electricity usage at home. Here are some tips to help you save electricity:</span><br></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"756d1a87-538e-4df2-b91b-b96aaf33467c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">1. Use Energy-Efficient Appliances: When purchasing new appliances, look for those with the Energy Star label. These appliances are designed to be more energy-efficient and can help you save electricity in the long run. Additionally, consider using smart power strips that can automatically turn off power to idle devices or appliances.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"07709011-ce43-496f-bc62-5d2047476514\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">2. Switch to LED Lighting: Replace traditional incandescent bulbs with energy-efficient LED bulbs. LED bulbs consume significantly less energy and have a longer lifespan, making them a cost-effective choice. Remember to turn off lights when not in use and make use of natural daylight whenever possible.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"c8e67cd8-01cb-4771-8722-771b3a9959a2\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">3. Adjust Thermostat Settings: Heating and cooling can account for a significant portion of your electricity usage. Set your thermostat to an appropriate temperature, such as 78Â°F (25.5Â°C) in the summer and 68Â°F (20Â°C) in the winter. Use fans and natural ventilation to stay comfortable and reduce the need for air conditioning.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"89b99c0e-6092-4f51-993d-d704f06de6ac\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">4. Unplug Electronics and Chargers: Even when not in use, electronics and chargers continue to draw power. Unplug devices such as televisions, computers, and phone chargers when they are not actively being used. Alternatively, use power strips and turn them off when not needed.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"2bc90882-0c0f-4420-927b-9ee39d9e29d4\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">5. Optimize Refrigerator Use: Ensure that your refrigerator is set to the recommended temperature (around 37Â°F or 3Â°C for the fridge and 0Â°F or -18Â°C for the freezer). Keep the refrigerator door closed as much as possible and avoid placing hot or warm food directly into the fridge. Regularly clean and maintain the coils to allow for efficient operation.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3884d6e4-1325-47bd-8164-c59f45fd8ea2\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">6. Use Natural Light and Ventilation: Utilize natural light during the day by opening curtains and blinds. This will reduce the need for artificial lighting. Similarly, open windows and use natural ventilation to cool your home instead of relying solely on air conditioning.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0ecf913b-0128-4ff9-847e-b330c16a8e1d\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">7. Conduct Regular Maintenance: Keep your appliances and electrical systems well-maintained to ensure optimal efficiency. Clean or replace air filters regularly, clean the lint filter in your dryer, and ensure that your home is properly insulated to reduce heat loss during winter months.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"01837320-49d2-478b-a752-cd70ca4eb464\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">8. Practice Energy-Efficient Cooking: When using the oven, try to cook multiple dishes at once to maximize its usage. Use lids on pots and pans to reduce cooking time and energy consumption. Additionally, consider using a microwave or toaster oven for smaller meals, as they consume less electricity than a full-sized oven.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"533756e7-0c3e-461f-bd0a-80c3def4276c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">9. Limit Water Heater Usage: Lower the temperature of your water heater to 120Â°F (49Â°C) to save energy. Consider insulating your water heater and pipes to reduce heat loss. Additionally, take shorter showers and fix any leaks in faucets or pipes to conserve both water and energy.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"50f9b99c-5f13-49cc-987d-ab42b04eb39c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">10. Educate Your Family: Encourage everyone in your household to be mindful of their energy usage. Teach them the importance of turning off lights when leaving a room, unplugging unused devices, and practicing energy-saving habits.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"fc52fe57-2f19-481f-badf-c0a0713fea99\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"2588194c-d878-40f4-8679-904010b5fdeb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By following these simple tips, you can make a significant impact in reducing your electricity consumption at home. Not only will you contribute to a greener environment, but you will also see a noticeable decrease in your electricity bills. Start implementing these energy-saving practices today and enjoy the benefits of a more sustainable and efficient home.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-1303145569.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  30th  August 2023', 1),
