(93, '0', 'Hohoe: Residents clash with police in Godenu; 3 feared dead, police vehicle set ablaze.', '', 'News', '<p><br></p><p>Tension is brewing in Godenu, a village near Hohoe in the Volta Region after the police allegedly opened fire on residents, leaving three persons dead and several others injured.</p><p><br></p><p>The incident happened on Wednesday morning, August 30, 2023, when the police attempted to arrest a man suspected of carrying Indian hemp from his farm.</p><p><br></p><p>The man escaped into one of the houses in the village on his motor bike, and the police allegedly began shooting indiscriminately, resulting in the death of three residents and injuries to several others. The police are alleged to have also burnt all motorbikes on sight.</p><p><br></p><p>In retaliation, some residents allegedly set one of the four police vehicles on fire.</p><p><br></p><p>The injured persons are receiving treatment at the hospital, while the body of the deceased has been sent to the morgue.</p><p><br></p><p>The MP for the area has been informed about the incident, and the police have launched an investigation.</p><p><br></p><p>The residents have locked themselves up in their rooms, fearing being shot if they come out.Narrating the incident to citinewsroom.com a resident named Francis Kakraba said, â€œIn the morning around 10:am, I heard some gunshots. I rushed out and saw some people screaming. The police after failing to arrest a farmer who was returning from his farm suspected to be carrying Indian hemp rushed to the community and started shooting. Some of their vehicles caught fire in the process. Some people sustained injuries and others have died.â€</p><p><br></p><p>The incident has sparked outrage among the residents, who are demanding justice for the victims. They are also calling for an end to police brutality in the area.</p><p><br></p><p>Source: Citi 97.3 FM</p><p>#revivalfm993&nbsp;</p><p>#revivalmorningdrive&nbsp;</p><p>#revivalpowersports</p>', '1693423893574.jpg', '', '', 'Source ', '  30th  August 2023', 1),
(94, '0', 'Getting your New Home rewired to code: How much will it cost?', '', 'electrical', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e09bb744-f9aa-4ab4-ab85-e7c68db4a134\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Title: Getting Your New Home Rewired to Code: How Much Will It Cost?</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"6ef2d811-0a48-412a-80bc-1a4c6dd542b3\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Introduction:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"99a02389-005c-404d-9ee8-12073ce34389\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">When moving into a new home, ensuring that the electrical wiring is up to code is essential for both safety and functionality. Rewiring a home to meet the latest electrical standards not only protects your investment but also ensures the well-being of your family. However, the cost of rewiring can vary based on several factors. This document aims to provide a comprehensive overview of the factors that influence the cost of getting your new home rewired to code.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ee33838c-6938-4649-9eab-305fa82bbe3c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Factors that Influence the Cost of Rewiring:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a538b69b-26f8-4285-8128-6bdf06428fa1\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">1. Size of the Home:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"177c267c-1619-44a0-856f-df48b8b201c2\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">The size of your home plays a significant role in determining the cost of rewiring. Larger homes generally require more electrical outlets, wiring, and circuit breakers, resulting in increased material and labor costs.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ef2739b8-5eb9-4411-b91a-10a05f151ae8\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">2. Age and Condition of the Existing Wiring:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8a3cdda7-7583-476a-8186-8f0e76c1baad\">Older homes often between 10 <wt-ignore uuid=\"a720b715-e7cc-4c98-9522-c450d8e2f9d6\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">and</wt-ignore> 15 years have outdated wiring systems that may not meet current safety standards. In such cases, rewiring becomes a necessity to ensure the electrical system is safe and reliable. The condition of the existing wiring also affects the cost, as damaged or deteriorated wiring may need to be replaced entirely. when an electrical system becomes to old it reduces the conductivity of the conductors which also cost a significant rise in electrical tarif.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f381553e-f438-418f-8447-87958f90b90f\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">3. Accessibility and Complexity:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"40ace2d9-7b31-4df4-9290-024efe60cd77\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">The accessibility of the wiring within the walls, ceilings, and floors can impact the cost of rewiring. If the wiring is easily accessible, the labor costs may be lower. However, if the wiring is hidden behind walls or in hard-to-reach areas, it may require additional time and effort, increasing the overall cost.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3413d387-ed01-46f7-9a8f-5a363920bcf4\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">4. Number of Rooms and Outlets:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"33fdf2a0-c320-42b0-a093-7a00829af104\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">The number of rooms and outlets in your home will affect the cost of rewiring. Each room requires wiring for lighting, switches, and electrical outlets. Additional outlets or specialized wiring for appliances, such as air conditioning units or home theaters, will also add to the total cost.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4f0e2c7d-5f55-4e2b-bd5e-77c48141f198\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">5. Electrical Panel Upgrade:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"531a34ae-050e-41e0-9422-65ac02124668\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In some cases, rewiring a home may require upgrading the electrical panel to accommodate the increased electrical load. If the existing panel is outdated or insufficient, it may need to be replaced, resulting in additional costs.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ac670b6b-6973-4808-a822-ef2dccd740e8\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">6. Local Regulations and Permits:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8213fdbd-8b74-462a-a821-bc069cd91aed\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Complying with local building codes and obtaining the necessary permits is crucial when rewiring a home. Permit fees and inspection costs should be considered when calculating the overall cost of the project.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"89177539-a8dd-4bce-84cf-20fd9c066ccb\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Cost Estimates:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"142529dc-8012-450f-8bda-1f6856e976f7\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">It is challenging to provide an exact cost estimate for rewiring a home, as it varies based on the factors mentioned above. On average, homeowners can expect to spend between $3,500 and $8,000 for a standard-sized home with moderate complexity. However, costs can increase significantly for larger homes or homes with extensive electrical needs.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d79373ae-84d0-4acc-b9d9-f16cfb62b7ae\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Conclusion:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d43cce09-9af0-4888-a576-97bc1c1da564\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"7ae1e84e-b006-4ff3-b2f7-fba997cba129\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Ensuring that your&nbsp; home is rewired to code is a vital investment in your safety and peace of mind. While the cost of rewiring can vary depending on several factors, it is crucial to prioritize electrical safety. Consulting with a licensed electrician and obtaining multiple quotes will help you determine the exact cost and scope of the project. Remember, the cost of rewiring is an investment in the long-term safety and functionality of your new home.</wt-ignore></p>', '10-Free-Online-Electrical-Courses-With-Certificates-In-2022.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  31st  August 2023', 1),
(95, '0', 'What is defilement? Here are some things you should know about defiling and its penalties', '', 'lifestyle', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ef0f92dc-5d38-4643-81c0-9d60c32c263e\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Introduction:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4e261faf-99eb-4043-9a74-c3c1f5bd5184\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Defilement refers to any unlawful sexual activity involving a person below the age of consent. In Ghana, the Criminal Offences Act, 1960 (Act 29), as amended, defines defilement as the willful and unlawful engagement of a person under the age of 16 years in any sexual activity, whether or not there is consent.</wt-ignore>  </p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"00c39f42-c9da-4546-9c89-eae286a4c383\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In Ghana, the law on defilement is designed to protect children from sexual abuse and exploitation. This document aims to provide a comprehensive understanding of the legal framework surrounding defilement in Ghana. It will cover the definition of defilement, the legal age of consent, penalties for offenders, and the legal remedies available to victims.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4855a4af-62ed-46bd-b329-24b79ee49fd1\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Definition of Defilement:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0fcd6ba5-d18e-470d-8a74-2adebd2d6da1\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Legal Age of Consent:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"09e91737-fc52-4733-bc13-fff7611ed8c1\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">The legal age of consent in Ghana is 16 years. Any sexual activity with a person below this age is considered defilement, regardless of whether the minor gave consent or not. It is important to note that the law does not recognize consent as a defense in cases of defilement involving a minor.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"7b646633-bcc3-45d4-8505-6b82f96ae526\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Penalties for Offenders:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"30724cfb-37c5-4360-acf3-789c603ddbdf\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Ghanaian law takes defilement very seriously, imposing strict penalties on offenders. Upon conviction, the offender may face imprisonment for a term not less than five years and not more than 25 years. In aggravated cases, where the victim is below 13 years or where the offender is a person in authority, the minimum sentence is raised to 7 years and can be extended to life imprisonment.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0d4a4e8b-18ec-4671-a482-cf88d1fa0169\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Legal Remedies for Victims:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ac0e2efc-f9f1-4883-9a8f-965bd8fdab87\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Ghanaian law recognizes the rights and protection of victims of defilement. Victims are entitled to seek legal remedies to obtain justice and support. They have the right to report the crime to the police, who are obligated to investigate and prosecute the offender. Victims can also seek medical and psychological support through government agencies and non-profit organizations working in the field of child protection.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"048387d0-c5cc-4dfd-b8f8-a528e04e9b32\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Conclusion:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d45aab5c-646a-44e9-811c-17fc87ddce25\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"ec5b214a-8de2-4fda-928a-17abbae33e1c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">The Ghanaian law on defilement is aimed at safeguarding the rights and well-being of children. It prohibits any sexual activity involving a person below the age of consent, regardless of consent. Offenders face severe penalties upon conviction, including imprisonment. Victims of defilement are encouraged to come forward and seek legal remedies to ensure justice is served and to access the necessary support services available. By upholding these laws, Ghana strives to protect its children and create a safe environment for their growth and development.</wt-ignore></p>', 'defiled-1.jpg', '', '', 'Source ', '  31st  August 2023', 1),
(96, '0', 'Factors to Consider When Planning a Building Project in Ghana', '', 'lifestyle', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"93f340ea-83a8-4de9-aa6c-64caf5f48276\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">When planning a building project in Ghana, there are several factors that need to be taken into consideration. These factors are crucial to ensure a successful and efficient construction process. Below are some key points to consider:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"566e55b0-1085-4b69-8f70-a784b261367b\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>1. Legal and Regulatory Requirements:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"fd8d32de-631d-4365-bdd6-12abd8a67a9b\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   It is essential to familiarize yourself with the legal and regulatory framework in Ghana. This includes understanding the building codes, permits, and licenses required for your project. Compliance with these regulations is important to avoid delays and penalties.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3d520b03-b04e-4b95-acb7-07c7943eb939\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>2. Site Selection:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4deef62c-aa67-4cd0-b463-0b99090f2240\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Choosing the right location is critical for the success of your building project. Factors to consider include accessibility, infrastructure availability, proximity to services, and potential environmental impacts. Conduct thorough site assessments to determine the suitability of the land.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0711e0e8-93eb-4149-8bdd-e99e7176704e\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>3. Local Materials and Construction Techniques:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"95539b35-62b7-4330-811d-8794a0a3d3dc\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Ghana has a rich variety of local building materials and construction techniques. Consider utilizing sustainable and locally available materials such as clay, timber, and bamboo. This not only supports the local economy but also ensures the durability and affordability of your project.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"fb258ce3-6128-4383-b58b-b0a82c60e290\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>4. Climate and Environmental Factors:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"984cfa19-4349-4fc9-954d-45442ab4102f\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Ghana experiences a tropical climate with varying rainfall patterns. Take into account the impact of the climate on the building design and materials. Consider factors like ventilation, insulation, and waterproofing to ensure the comfort and longevity of the structure.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5e8e38e9-9112-4ee8-9b4c-827ec9c5bed3\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>5. Cultural Considerations:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"47b1e689-7e12-4ea4-86a8-864728083fe6\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Ghana has a diverse cultural heritage, and it is important to respect and integrate local customs and traditions. Consult with local communities and stakeholders to understand any cultural considerations that may influence the design and construction of the building.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"73010fd2-2b70-46d2-95ed-5679476feabc\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>6. Infrastructure and Utilities:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"03996d60-1980-49ad-88f8-213b3b980311\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Assess the availability and reliability of essential infrastructure and utilities such as electricity, water, and sewage systems. Ensure that the project can be connected to these services and plan for any necessary upgrades or installations.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"cd0356f4-4aeb-446b-b004-bdcb28e6f8e7\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>7. Project Management and Contractors:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"cf2bedfc-408b-4ac0-82e5-73c22da23dce\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Engage reputable and experienced contractors and project managers who are familiar with the local construction industry. This will help ensure effective coordination, quality control, and adherence to timelines.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8bc24c98-eb34-462b-806c-4b82c6cc44fd\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>8. Budget and Financing:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"cfd08c90-c95d-4874-9a72-914c2d08c024\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Develop a realistic budget for your building project, considering all the necessary expenses such as land acquisition, permits, materials, labor, and contingencies. Explore various financing options to secure the necessary funds for the project.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"abb99bb5-b1e4-4aaa-a61b-d4e9dbbe6356\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>9. Sustainability and Energy Efficiency:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"809db823-30b8-4415-adfe-dda84021cf2e\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">   Building sustainably and incorporating energy-efficient features can reduce operational costs and have a positive impact on the environment. Consider using renewable energy sources, efficient lighting systems, and water-saving technologies.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"7cc09e9c-0043-4e7c-bd40-85396a8c8e29\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>10. Safety and Security:</b></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"1640f47d-ae4f-40ac-98c4-0ac8d525bb91\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">    Prioritize safety and security measures throughout the construction process. This includes implementing proper safety protocols, providing appropriate personal protective equipment, and ensuring the security of the construction site.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e68dbf57-0d07-4847-9367-5f6e51a66032\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"a824072e-f873-405a-a48d-42865eeba79d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By considering these factors when planning a building project in Ghana, you will be better equipped to navigate the complexities and challenges of construction in the country. Remember to collaborate with local experts and stakeholders to ensure a successful outcome.</wt-ignore></p>', '925c3a19fed0c3fe66b41e618b296061--architecture-design-accra.jpg', '', '', 'Source ', '  31st  August 2023', 1),
