(110, '0', 'Factors to Consider When Planning a Wedding in Ghana', '', 'lifestyle', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3e1fce11-f7c4-42a8-8b79-35c9d4304ebe\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Planning a wedding can be an exciting yet challenging task, especially when it comes to organizing a wedding in Ghana. From cultural traditions to logistical considerations, there are several factors that need to be taken into account to ensure a successful and memorable wedding celebration. Here are some essential factors to consider when planning a wedding in Ghana:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"650a3416-109f-4c35-bc0a-74f72dbef791\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">1. Budget: Determining a realistic budget is the first step in planning any wedding. Consider all the necessary expenses, including venue, catering, decorations, photography, and entertainment. Ghanaian weddings often involve extensive guest lists, so it\'s crucial to allocate funds accordingly.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a6d7a778-3d22-48ad-963b-e4cef34f3e8a\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">2. Date and Venue: Choosing the right wedding date and venue is crucial. Consider the weather, availability of your desired venue, and any cultural or religious events that might clash with your wedding date. Popular wedding venues in Ghana include hotels, event centers, and traditional locations such as beaches or gardens.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3365d995-fa99-4560-b734-7aa661375226\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">3. Guest List: Ghanaian weddings are typically large and involve extended family and friends. Prepare a comprehensive guest list and consider the capacity of your chosen venue. Also, keep in mind any cultural expectations or obligations when inviting guests.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"1820c889-ff15-457b-a3c3-b29684e7d26c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">4. Traditional Customs: Ghanaian weddings are rich in cultural traditions and customs. Research and understand these traditions to incorporate them into your wedding ceremony and reception. This may include the traditional engagement ceremony (knocking), pouring of libation, and the exchange of gifts.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"70c335bc-6e92-4843-a6f7-0a45a40eb043\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">5. Wedding Attire: The choice of wedding attire is an essential aspect of a Ghanaian wedding. Traditional Ghanaian outfits, such as Kente or Ankara fabrics, are popular choices for both the bride and groom. However, many couples also opt for Western-style wedding attire.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"fdfe39a5-cd2c-4cc1-8a78-7366c2e4a26a\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">6. Food and Catering: Ghanaian cuisine is diverse and flavorful. Consider including traditional Ghanaian dishes in your wedding menu, such as jollof rice, fried rice, banku, and fufu. Ensure that your chosen caterer can accommodate the dietary preferences of your guests.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"dc41f362-23b3-4a19-98eb-47fedec055e3\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">7. Music and Entertainment: Music plays a central role in Ghanaian weddings. Hire a live band or DJ to provide entertainment throughout the celebration. Incorporate traditional Ghanaian music and dance styles, such as highlife, hiplife, or azonto, to create a vibrant and festive atmosphere.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"61de606a-43b5-422d-ba32-9e68b8d30ad5\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">8. Photography and Videography: Hiring a professional photographer and videographer is essential to capture the precious moments of your wedding day. Look for experienced professionals who are familiar with Ghanaian weddings and can capture the cultural elements beautifully.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"061d9f1d-1756-46fa-8488-017cd46273b0\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">9. Wedding Planner: Consider hiring a wedding planner who specializes in Ghanaian weddings. They can provide valuable guidance, handle logistical details, and ensure a smooth and stress-free wedding planning process.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"55094b5c-b4d8-4b72-85e4-f7ab2f949fbc\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">10. Marriage Registration: Don\'t forget to complete the legal requirements for marriage registration in Ghana. Obtain the necessary documents and follow the procedures outlined by the Registrar General\'s Department.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f7e7f219-8cf4-47f5-89d3-255601cafad0\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"719049f3-46ed-4d24-b659-0314f350a9bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By considering these factors, you can ensure that your wedding in Ghana is a truly memorable and culturally enriching experience for both you and your guests. Plan ahead, pay attention to details, and embrace the beauty of Ghanaian traditions to create a wedding celebration that reflects your love and commitment.</wt-ignore></p>', 'OIP.jpg', '', '', 'Source ', '  4th  September 2023', 1),
(111, '0', 'The DIY Guide to Fixing Damaged Electrical Bulbs like a pro', '', 'electrical', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"bc60c675-fbc6-4a30-835f-da8928797510\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In this DIY guide, we will walk you through the process of changing damaged electrical bulbs in your home. Whether you\'re a beginner or have some experience with DIY projects, this step-by-step guide will help you safely and effectively replace damaged bulbs, ensuring a well-lit and functional space.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"55be274d-1b71-4c52-9bd6-ffa4ef1a9cef\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Tools and Materials Required:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"725ee07b-2819-4362-a5f6-f321c9c7d060\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Before we dive into the process of changing damaged electrical bulbs, it\'s important to gather the necessary tools and materials. Here\'s what you\'ll need:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5beb99be-c3db-4688-8725-3b8726cf0526\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">1. Replacement bulbs: Make sure to choose bulbs that are compatible with your existing fixtures and meet the required wattage.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"80fd47b0-2e97-4e86-8c2a-cc6dc8f885ea\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">2. Step ladder or sturdy stool: This will help you reach bulbs that are located in higher fixtures.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ca217fbe-4cd4-4605-8fc4-47b8764d75b4\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">3. Safety gloves: To protect your hands from any potential accidents or electrical shocks.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"1ce94ce7-3111-4664-9a51-f8ae0a997142\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">4. Safety glasses: A must-have to protect your eyes from any glass shards that may break during the process.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"063f0ef9-012e-4fb9-a900-472afefb67ff\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">5. Voltage tester: This will help ensure that the power supply to the fixture is turned off before you start working.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"525d2716-9bc3-40b4-8921-25523cbe1d06\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step-by-Step Guide:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"01179249-7986-42f4-81ee-871dc68a80d0\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Now that you have all the necessary tools and materials, let\'s get started with the process of changing damaged electrical bulbs:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"de08595f-19b0-47ad-8fa3-55e64cc6d53e\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step 1: Turn Off the Power Supply:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d963f6a0-09fa-4c60-8b46-970f83661858\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Before you begin the process, ensure that the power supply to the fixture is turned off. Use a voltage tester to confirm that there is no electrical current flowing to the bulb socket.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a5dd468c-0917-41d7-b428-27ecb82d752c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step 2: Allow the Bulb to Cool Down:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"63457a2a-5fc4-4c67-92c2-5c496b5055a7\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">If the damaged bulb was recently in use, give it some time to cool down before attempting to remove it. This will prevent any accidental burns or injuries.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5652c97a-2559-419b-a1a2-5f96d88ddf0f\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step 3: Remove the Old Bulb:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0cc14ebd-0ead-40e7-99b4-a87df8456f3c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Carefully grip the damaged bulb and gently twist it counterclockwise until it loosens from the socket. Once loose, carefully pull it straight out.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8a1fade4-bf2a-4f40-a164-94f9720deaed\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step 4: Inspect the Socket:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"072f7162-aca5-4f37-8def-9d367ecf4c32\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">After removing the old bulb, take a moment to inspect the socket for any signs of damage or corrosion. If you notice any issues, consult a professional electrician for further assistance.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"fb7085d8-d5bf-40ec-942d-2a1ac7b296c9\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step 5: Install the New Bulb:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e4dc08c4-c543-4b35-a0f4-3e3521967405\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Take the replacement bulb and align the base with the socket. Gently push the bulb into the socket and rotate it clockwise until it is securely in place. Avoid over-tightening, as this can damage the fixture.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b5d7d863-4049-4fe2-83a3-e7e6586771ee\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step 6: Test the Bulb:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"43651a8d-b38d-4f80-887e-4029211596a0\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Once the new bulb is installed, turn on the power supply and test the bulb to ensure it is functioning correctly. If it doesn\'t light up, double-check the connection and consult a professional if needed.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"581498dd-b4e9-4eab-afaa-8ba42ab4c904\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Conclusion:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9b52a2b2-1494-49f0-858e-8f69b301fbfa\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8434c8ab-d727-4949-99e4-ed957694a9d5\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By following this DIY guide, you should now be able to confidently change damaged electrical bulbs in your home. Remember to always prioritize safety by turning off the power supply, using safety gloves and glasses, and consulting a professional if you encounter any issues. With a little bit of knowledge and the right tools, you can easily maintain a well-lit and safe environment in your home.</wt-ignore></p>', 'R (1).jpg', '', '', 'Source ', '  5th  September 2023', 1),
(112, '0', 'Bimbilla: EP College of Education Principal dies in tragic accident', '', 'News', '<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The Principal of the EP College of Education in Bimbilla, Professor James Gurundow, has tragically lost his life in a car accident.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The incident occurred while he was returning from a funeral in Jamani, located in the Bono region, en route to Tamale on Saturday night, according to&nbsp;<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Citi News</span>&nbsp;sources.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">His vehicle collided with another car coming from the opposite direction.Although there were four occupants in his car during the accident, Professor Gurundow was the sole fatality.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1em;