(121, '0', 'Negative habits that weaken your mental health', '', 'lifestyle', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4fbedd7b-7414-4ba1-bf28-fb9df0211cc2\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In order to maintain a strong and healthy mind, it is important to be aware of the habits that can weaken our mental well-being. While some habits may seem harmless, they can actually have a negative impact on our mental strength. By identifying and addressing these habits, we can work towards developing a stronger and more resilient mindset. Here are some common habits that make you mentally weak:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ed4b4bc8-559a-43c6-a61c-48d07e034c9e\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>1. Negative self-talk:</b> Constantly engaging in negative self-talk can be detrimental to our mental health. When we constantly put ourselves down or focus on our shortcomings, it can lead to feelings of low self-esteem and self-doubt. It is important to practice self-compassion and positive self-talk in order to build mental strength.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"7c7b31f1-e1b5-4ac7-9726-dadbc0a38e69\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>2. Procrastination:</b> Putting off tasks and delaying important responsibilities can create unnecessary stress and anxiety. Procrastination not only leads to a lack of productivity, but it also undermines our confidence and self-discipline. By developing good time management skills and breaking tasks into smaller, manageable chunks, we can overcome the habit of procrastination.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a84223f1-68e0-4363-ae68-2a835ebe04e0\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>3. Dwelling on the past:</b> Constantly dwelling on past mistakes or regrets can hinder our ability to move forward and grow. It is important to acknowledge and learn from our past experiences, but dwelling on them excessively can prevent us from living in the present and focusing on the future. Letting go of the past and embracing the present moment is essential for mental strength.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5300edec-2f97-46da-97c8-d126382d919b\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>4. Seeking validation from others:</b> Relying on external validation for our self-worth can make us mentally weak. When we constantly seek approval and validation from others, we give away our power and allow others to define our self-esteem. Building a strong sense of self and valuing our own opinions and worth is crucial for mental resilience.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4159a1be-4feb-4008-8213-4e992e3be5db\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>5. Avoiding challenges:</b> Avoiding challenges and staying within our comfort zone may feel safe, but it hinders our personal growth and mental strength. Embracing challenges and pushing ourselves outside of our comfort zone allows us to develop new skills, build confidence, and overcome obstacles. Embracing challenges is a key habit for mental strength.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"99e309ab-9539-47bc-b7da-1c8cd40171f0\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>6. Constantly comparing ourselves to others:</b> Comparing ourselves to others can lead to feelings of inadequacy and undermine our self-esteem. Each person\'s journey is unique, and comparing ourselves to others only serves to distract us from our own progress and achievements. Focusing on our own personal growth and celebrating our own successes is vital for mental strength.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8a35b3fc-8d23-45e0-b3d9-e6c8800b19f3\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>7. Excessive screen time:</b> Spending excessive time on screens, whether it be on our phones, tablets, or computers, can negatively impact our mental health. It can lead to feelings of isolation, decreased productivity, and increased stress. Taking breaks from screens, engaging in activities that promote mindfulness and connection, and setting healthy boundaries with technology are important for maintaining mental well-being.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"6df6fea5-0c66-451e-9cd0-155a9283351c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"86561a99-094d-428d-8614-e42e0b2a170a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By being aware of these habits that make us mentally weak, we can take proactive steps to address them and develop a stronger mindset. It is important to remember that building mental strength is a continuous process and requires consistent effort and self-reflection. With time and practice, we can cultivate habits that promote mental resilience and well-being.</wt-ignore></p>', 'main-qimg-51ffd6598c39155b5429824bad485cb2.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  10th  September 2023', 1),
