(140, '0', 'When planning rent in Ghana, consider the following factors', '', 'mechanical', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ac30bbdb-dd58-4aab-89a9-920ed65043f7\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">When planning to rent a property in Ghana, it is crucial to consider various factors to ensure a smooth and satisfactory renting experience. The following are the key factors that should be taken into account:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"64202b34-38d7-4915-b31e-8de3523dfce2\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>1. Location: </b>The location of the property plays a significant role in determining the rent. In Ghana, the rental prices can vary significantly depending on the area. Properties located in prime areas or close to amenities such as schools, hospitals, shopping centers, and transportation hubs tend to have higher rental rates compared to those in less desirable locations.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"6e17f356-a3ea-4535-aeaa-d510e7657b27\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>2. Property Type and Size:</b> The type and size of the property also play a crucial role in determining the rent. The rental price for a detached house or a luxury apartment will be higher compared to a smaller apartment or a shared accommodation. It is essential to consider your needs and budget when selecting a property type and size.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"46e65bcd-ffde-4b68-a1d2-9ca3a943b041\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>3. Amenities and Facilities:</b> The availability of amenities and facilities within a property can impact the rent. Properties with amenities such as swimming pools, gyms, parking spaces, and security features often command higher rental prices. It is essential to evaluate the amenities and facilities provided and assess whether they align with your preferences and requirements.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ad50af3c-3e8f-42f8-9a89-d102d8c37a3a\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>4. Condition of the Property:</b> The condition of the property is another important factor to consider. Well-maintained and modern properties generally have higher rental rates compared to older and poorly maintained ones. It is advisable to inspect the property thoroughly and consider any necessary repairs or renovations when determining the rent.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3116b718-7a23-42c6-8cd7-341c9ab12f19\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>5. Market Demand:</b> The demand for rental properties in a particular area can influence the rental prices. Areas with high demand and low supply often have higher rental rates. It is advisable to research the rental market in the desired location to understand the prevailing rental rates and demand.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"94979851-a642-47b5-be54-ca1f45f42bcb\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>6. Rental Terms:</b> It is crucial to consider the rental terms when planning rent in Ghana. Factors such as the duration of the lease, payment terms, and any additional fees or charges should be carefully reviewed. It is important to ensure that the rental terms are fair and reasonable before finalizing the agreement.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"49603bfb-d32f-48c7-8524-c019c1f92f13\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>7. Legal Requirements:</b> Familiarizing yourself with the legal requirements and regulations regarding rental properties in Ghana is essential. This includes understanding the rights and responsibilities of both tenants and landlords, as well as any applicable rental laws. Compliance with legal requirements is vital to ensure a smooth and legally binding rental agreement.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"09dd119d-d904-4bb8-9457-50320b9a472f\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"538daaa3-f4bc-4437-9a18-2aa8856f5f50\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By considering these factors, you can make an informed decision when planning the rent for a property in Ghana. Taking the time to evaluate these aspects will help you find a suitable rental property that meets your needs and budget while ensuring a fair and mutually beneficial rental agreement.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-149060607.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  17th  September 2023', 1),
(142, '0', 'Planning to buy furniture? Here are some things to consider', '', '', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e939b8b8-5400-4c12-a4f8-6234f09ecc58\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\" style=\"text-align: left; \"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">When it comes to buying furniture for your home, several important factors need to be considered. Taking the time to plan and make informed decisions can ensure that you choose the right pieces that not only fit your style but also meet your practical needs. Here are some key factors to consider when planning to buy furniture for your home:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"df2c66d3-967c-4f97-87f9-2cdbadc02e6c\" style=\"text-align: left; \"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>1. Budget:</b> Before embarking on any furniture shopping, it is essential to establish a budget. Determine how much you are willing to spend on furniture and stick to it. This will help you make more informed decisions and prevent overspending.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"2b652560-2c0e-4ec3-9ea5-d546bd7af181\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>2. Room Measurements:</b> Measure the rooms where the furniture will be placed. This step is crucial to ensure that the furniture you purchase fits well and doesn\'t overcrowd the space. Take note of doorways, windows, and any other architectural features that may affect the placement of furniture.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"1d1bd7e2-e8ef-4a7d-bba8-071be84d64eb\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>3. Functionality:</b> Consider the function of the furniture you are planning to buy. For example, if you\'re buying a sofa, think about whether you need it to be a comfortable lounging area or if it will primarily be used for seating guests. Understanding the primary purpose of the furniture will help guide your choices.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"da94e5df-994e-4022-a6a2-f9779261450d\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>4. Style and Aesthetic:</b> Think about the overall style and aesthetic you want to achieve in your home. Consider the existing decor and choose furniture that complements it. Whether your style is modern, traditional, or eclectic, select pieces that align with your personal taste.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"7476d60a-0bb0-4aca-95b2-7e5d4bf0506a\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>5. Quality and Durability:</b> Investing in high-quality furniture is essential for longevity. Check the materials used, construction methods, and overall craftsmanship of the piece. Ensure that the furniture is durable and built to withstand regular use.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e0bb826f-85a4-4c3c-b8a5-6a849a32de81\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>6. Comfort:</b> Comfort is a crucial factor, especially for furniture you\'ll be using frequently, such as sofas, chairs, and beds. Test out furniture before buying, if possible, to ensure that it provides the level of comfort you desire.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8ad0d42d-406e-4443-aaf3-7ce480b85d4e\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">7. Maintenance and </wt-ignore>Care:</b><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Consider the maintenance requirements of the furniture. Some materials may need special care or regular upkeep. Determine if you are willing to commit to the necessary maintenance routines.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"168b7819-1be0-449d-9081-03838a3d93d5\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>8. Eco-Friendly and Sustainable Options:</b> If sustainability is important to you, consider furniture made from eco-friendly materials or from sustainable sources. Look for certifications such as Forest Stewardship Council (FSC) or Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design (LEED) to ensure the furniture meets certain environmental standards.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4e7f60d4-9055-45d8-a18c-ad082f67f35e\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>9. Delivery and Assembly:</b> Check the delivery options and assembly requirements before making a purchase. Some furniture pieces may require professional assembly, while others may be delivered fully assembled. Factor in the cost and convenience of delivery and assembly when making your decision.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"14fe4af2-0d5e-4ac5-bc7a-96fb70a0304c\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><b>10. Return Policy and Warranty:</b> Lastly, familiarize yourself with the return policy and warranty offered by the furniture retailer. It\'s important to have peace of mind knowing that you can return or exchange the furniture if it doesn\'t meet your expectations or if any issues arise.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"39428e9d-9bfa-4521-afdd-d477edc5543e\" style=\"text-align: left; \"><wt-ignore uuid=\"8c8a53d7-b1d8-4385-91b4-f3c9a7858e1d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By considering these factors when planning to buy furniture for your home, you can make well-informed decisions that will result in a comfortable, functional, and aesthetically pleasing living space. Take your time, do thorough research, and choose furniture that reflects your personal style while meeting your practical needs.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-1186690832.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  17th  September 2023', 1),
(143, '0', 'This is everything you need to know about backflow and how to prevent it', 'This-is-everything-you-need-to-know-about-backflow-and-how-to-prevent-it', 'plumbing', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a79f0698-5194-4938-87d5-13dfcf23e151\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">Backflow in plumbing is a common issue that can cause significant problems if not properly understood and prevented. In this document, we will explain what backflow is, its causes, potential consequences, and most importantly, how to prevent it.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"67ebdf6d-fe4e-42a8-81e7-3df878ecb409\"><strong>What is backflow?</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0f8b6183-7c18-4b81-ba2c-0c6b7bf255bb\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"568cbb6a-31fe-4fcc-be58-66c7199b9165\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Backflow occurs when the flow of water in a plumbing system is reversed, causing the contaminated or non-potable water to enter the clean water supply. This can happen due to a sudden drop in water pressure or a back siphonage caused by negative pressure in the system. Backflow can also occur due to a backpressure, which happens when the pressure of non-potable water exceeds that of the clean water supply.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"eb5c8e46-134b-4465-a12f-0ad708599a3a\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"568cbb6a-31fe-4fcc-be58-66c7199b9165\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">There are several causes of backflow, including cross-connections between potable and non-potable water sources. These cross-connections can occur in various ways, such as when a garden hose is submerged in a pool, or when a hose is left connected to a chemical sprayer. These cross-connections can create a pathway for contaminated water to flow back into the clean water supply.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"03994867-52ef-49b4-9e26-45721a5382ec\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"568cbb6a-31fe-4fcc-be58-66c7199b9165\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">The consequences of backflow can be severe. Contaminated water entering the clean water supply can pose serious health risks, as it may contain bacteria, chemicals, or other harmful substances. In addition to health concerns, backflow can also damage plumbing fixtures, appliances, and pipes, leading to costly repairs.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"224d0847-f725-4273-b8a5-a550d259c724\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"568cbb6a-31fe-4fcc-be58-66c7199b9165\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Preventing backflow is crucial to maintaining the safety and integrity of the plumbing system. One of the most effective ways to prevent backflow is by installing backflow prevention devices. These devices, such as backflow preventer valves, are designed to allow water to flow in one direction only, preventing any reverse flow.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"17fa661b-d7ee-44d8-9b11-c842aab4302c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"568cbb6a-31fe-4fcc-be58-66c7199b9165\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Regular maintenance and inspection of plumbing systems is also essential in preventing backflow. This includes checking for any cross-connections and ensuring that all plumbing fixtures and appliances are properly installed and functioning correctly. It is also important to be cautious when connecting hoses to different water sources and to disconnect them when not in use.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"1e3dc87d-7b4a-4fdd-8e18-529bb3bf3b78\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"568cbb6a-31fe-4fcc-be58-66c7199b9165\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In conclusion, backflow in plumbing can have serious consequences and should not be taken lightly. Understanding the causes and potential risks of backflow is essential in preventing its occurrence. By implementing proper prevention measures, such as installing backflow prevention devices and conducting regular maintenance, the risk of backflow can be significantly reduced, ensuring the safety and quality of the water supply.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-851809952.jpg', '', '', 'Remember to Share this video', '  17th  September 2023', 1),
(145, '0', 'RTU defeats Hearts of Oak in the opening game of the Ghana Premier League', 'RTU-defeats-Hearts-of-Oak-in-the-opening-game-of-the-Ghana-Premier-League', 'sports', '<p>At the Aliu Mahama Sports Stadium, Real Tamale United (RTU) defeated Hearts of Oak 1-0 in the first game of the 2023/24 Ghana Premier League on Friday night.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b6944542-a01c-48f7-b8e7-9fa4f5514967\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5d94774b-7168-45f5-9f92-f22e31ade6c6\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">This is the fourth time in the last three seasons that the \'Pride of the North\' have beaten the Phobians, thanks to Owusu Afriyie\'s stoppage-time winner.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"372578d6-0648-4f70-a026-d644da5ea6ba\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"55845430-8021-4789-896f-dc030bb1f9ef\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">RTU had a number of chances in the first half, despite being fairly dominated by the home side.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f3f23e3b-71de-4470-8842-61ce32b5a610\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"d0423776-ade6-4b72-acde-21e9ef27e00f\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Changes in formation and personnel improved Hearts of Oak\'s performance in the second half.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"32d47f97-2b77-4c25-bd00-823fbfd67dc4\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"382b6a5f-1ed4-4861-bb1e-c6a70a33aec2\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">At halftime, it looked like the game would end in a goalless draw in the capital of the Northern Region, but the hosts dug deep to win.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"33973fc4-1374-4745-ace3-115d45931083\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">rowd the victory. It was poor defensive work from the Phobians resulting in the goal.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"32d47f97-2b77-4c25-bd00-823fbfd67dc4\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"382b6a5f-1ed4-4861-bb1e-c6a70a33aec2\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"></wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"218aa192-3400-4ab1-b7a2-cc82f3bae4b3\">Hearts of Oak will next host Nsoatreman in the second round while RTU play as guests <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-danger-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-danger-default/50 hover:bg-bg-danger-light-default\" data-issueid=\"c263a7a8-c854-42cc-8a07-09693beb7494\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text to\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:of\">to</span> Bofoakwa Tano. Watch the highlights below</p>', 'Hearts-of-Oak-1.jpg', '', '', '<iframe width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Lj5rzaKq010\" title=\"Real Tamale United 1:0 Accra Hearts of Oak| Highlights | betPawa Premier League\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '  18th  September 2023', 1),
