(153, '0', 'Step-by-Step Guide to Repair Your Old Furniture', 'Step-by-Step-Guide-to-Repair-Your-Old-Furniture', 'mechanical', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"aa6c73c2-438d-4cfb-9cf5-93531aa62107\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"20c2eabf-f15a-4625-b63b-1fb7398436fb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Why</wt-ignore> do you need to </strong><span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"da2c797c-d9ba-4ed9-bbf2-9d93ce2898fb\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text repair\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\"><strong>repair</strong></span><strong> your <wt-ignore uuid=\"5f69ddd0-df07-406b-bb3d-c91f692f3258\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">old</wt-ignore> <wt-ignore uuid=\"0a8ad247-8673-4ce1-ae02-1211c5b80805\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">furniture?</wt-ignore> </strong>Repairing your old furniture helps to keep it in <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"a7f43404-c591-4b94-b5d6-b860f78f68bd\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text good\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">good</span> condition and <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-danger-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-danger-default/50 hover:bg-bg-danger-light-default\" data-issueid=\"840bd3fd-703f-43f8-9c5b-7a9801ae632f\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text extend\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:extends\">extend</span> <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"447c8c34-fa85-4a7c-b511-3d41d52e1ff2\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text the life of the pieces.\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">the life of the pieces.</span> It also saves money in the long run, as repairs are often cheaper than buying <wt-ignore uuid=\"09c0d966-1c82-407d-a5af-f68f5030b182\" source=\"wt-feature-dismissed\">new</wt-ignore> furniture. Additionally, repairing your furniture can <wt-ignore uuid=\"774d3274-c003-4c22-92ec-efdbac726d10\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">help preserve</wt-ignore> its historical value.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b644fdeb-89d5-483b-9d70-7ff736d67460\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"f5a427ab-ffe9-42f8-84bc-31c24ac0319d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">We will walk you through the steps to repair your old furniture like a pro in this article.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9aec7286-9726-4a46-b27e-d5cc042f7685\"><strong>Step 1: Assess the Damage</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5cacacde-9e02-42a3-9d9d-bc7b952753ca\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Begin by thoroughly examining the furniture to identify any visible damage or areas that require repair. Look for scratches, dents, loose joints, or worn-out upholstery. Take note of all the issues to address during the repair process.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0d74154f-701b-4dd0-99e3-60ff0065700c\"><strong>Step 2: Gather the Necessary Tools and Materials</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"951d6492-fcf2-4bae-8c6b-5013097d7f23\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Before starting the repair, gather the appropriate tools and materials. This may include screwdrivers, wood glue, sandpaper, clamps, nails, a hammer, upholstery fabric, or any other items specific to the type of repair needed.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3f003876-dbbd-439f-ada3-1210498ddecf\">Before we move to the next step remember to follow me on <wt-ignore uuid=\"c85cb52a-d4e4-4875-b771-0d4f91b4adbb\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Facebook.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f0ac7852-b054-4a25-921d-9be6a4211490\"><strong>Step 3: Clean and Prepare the Surface</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0fe6daf4-2699-4415-a372-3eb3f4455236\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Clean the furniture surface using a mild detergent and warm water to remove any dirt or grime. If there are any existing finishes or coatings, you may need to strip them off using a suitable stripping agent. Sand the surface lightly to create a smooth and clean area for repair.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"2247328a-1d71-46aa-8492-1ebf289fdd5b\"><strong>Step 4: Repair Loose Joints</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"1eb1a3f5-b8b6-4140-9273-06df546b4c30\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">If there are any loose joints or connections, apply wood glue to the affected areas and firmly press the pieces together. Use clamps to hold the joints in place until the glue dries completely. Remove any excess glue with a damp cloth.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"538aaf43-aec2-445a-a74c-5d546dd125bd\"><strong>Step 5: Fix Scratches and Dents</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"2b47b302-9a4a-45d9-910b-9f31601c7205\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">To repair scratches or dents, apply a suitable wood filler or putty to the damaged area. Use a putty knife to spread the filler evenly and remove any excess. Allow the filler to dry completely, and then sand the surface until it is smooth and level with the rest of the furniture.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a449cd82-c98e-44f8-9562-133187022c3d\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Step 6: Refinish or Repaint</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ac431cf7-1c75-4994-8d6d-1c9db6740f0c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">If your furniture requires a new finish or paint, choose a suitable product based on the type of material and desired outcome. Follow the manufacturer\'s instructions for application and drying times. Apply multiple coats if necessary, sanding lightly between each coat for a smooth finish.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"988839d7-98fe-4a4d-92e3-08df7789e60d\"><strong>Step 7: Reupholster, if Needed</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4b92b515-55dc-45d6-82bd-39ef1a745710\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">If your furniture has worn-out or damaged upholstery, consider reupholstering it. Remove the old fabric carefully, and then measure and cut the new fabric to fit the furniture. Use a staple gun to secure the fabric in place, ensuring a tight and wrinkle-free finish.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"43223d86-22cc-4383-b13e-341aaf49a9ea\"><strong>Step 8: Final Touches and Maintenance</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d7d3dae0-0fd9-4f15-8521-3ecff031cb0a\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Once the repairs and refinishing are complete, inspect the furniture for any remaining issues. Tighten any loose screws or hardware and ensure all components are securely in place. Add any final touches, such as new hardware or decorative elements. Regularly maintain and clean your repaired furniture to prolong its lifespan.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ad8f16df-3081-499b-8f96-421c95a9b2d1\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"32e4db95-5aba-42b4-ac05-54d196790077\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By following these step-by-step instructions, you can effectively repair your old furniture and restore its functionality and appearance. Remember to take your time, work carefully, and seek professional assistance if needed.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-1309119384.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  19th  September 2023', 1),
(154, '0', 'Factors to consider when planning plumbing work for a new home', 'Factors-to-consider-when-planning-plumbing-work-for-a-new-home', 'plumbing', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"95b5e9a0-f1fa-4ad8-9f0c-6f1694288784\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">When planning the plumbing works for your new home, there are several important factors that you need to consider. These factors will not only ensure that your plumbing system is efficient and functional but also help you avoid potential issues in the future. Here are some key factors to keep in mind:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9fa3cd13-adc6-4b88-a5ad-7b3041917168\"><strong>1. Layout and Design:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"61ef0d84-81a7-4507-b359-cf8b4da884d4\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">The first factor to consider is the layout and design of your new home. This includes the placement of bathrooms, kitchens, and laundry rooms. It is important to carefully plan the location of these areas to ensure the most efficient flow of water and waste throughout the house.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"db5c8c35-830b-401c-b3bb-75e6338f9c46\"><strong>2. Water Supply:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"788787f6-54d4-4ec0-8dc4-603ac858464b\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Another crucial factor is the availability and quality of the water supply. You need to determine whether you will be connected to a public water supply or if you will rely on a well. Additionally, testing the water quality is essential to ensure it is safe for consumption and will not damage your plumbing system.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"c9df4b0b-eb33-46ec-9268-c10657e2ad9e\"><strong>3. Pipe Material:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"40618752-6489-4e29-8676-c7062c303706\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Choosing the right pipe material is essential for the longevity of your plumbing system. There are various options available, including copper, PVC, PEX, and galvanized steel. Each material has its own advantages and disadvantages, so it\'s important to consider factors such as cost, durability, and compatibility with the local climate.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b1286a83-0e14-4782-bfc1-9e87c0139221\"><strong>4. Drainage System:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"96574dff-9c70-4b9c-b47d-82ad510f573d\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">An efficient drainage system is crucial to prevent water damage and maintain a healthy living environment. Make sure to plan the drainage system carefully, including the installation of proper slope and venting. It is also important to consider the local building codes and regulations regarding drainage systems.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ea06c1ad-cdd8-4013-a80c-35f1bba8d493\"><strong>5. Water Efficiency:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b7e2f316-aa87-42f5-848e-c0d34cb5c388\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In today\'s environmentally conscious world, water efficiency is a significant factor to consider. Installing low-flow fixtures, such as toilets, faucets, and showerheads, can significantly reduce water consumption without compromising performance. Additionally, consider incorporating a rainwater harvesting system to conserve water and reduce your water bills.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"fb3d2d78-8162-4044-b3fe-c8d4026c9bf4\"><strong>6. Accessibility:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"cdcc262e-6d46-4758-a9b5-22a12000faaa\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">When planning your plumbing system, it\'s crucial to consider accessibility. Ensure that shut-off valves, cleanouts, and other plumbing components are easily accessible for maintenance and repairs. This will save you time and money in the long run, as it will be easier to address any issues that may arise.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9793b411-5ead-496c-9a97-0acfad57882a\"><strong>7. Professional Installation:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0df12f3e-3861-4467-8b9e-271d7ccfec73\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Lastly, it is highly recommended to hire a professional plumber for the installation of your plumbing system. They have the expertise and knowledge to ensure that everything is done correctly and up to code. Hiring a professional will give you peace of mind and minimize the risk of future plumbing problems.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"6ebc7bdc-1313-4a46-8ecb-d515f6ec061e\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cb7db3a-029d-4922-ba66-d375d2de5534\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In conclusion, planning the plumbing works for your new home requires careful consideration of various factors. By taking into account the layout, water supply, pipe material, drainage system, water efficiency, accessibility, and professional installation, you can ensure a well-designed and functional plumbing system. Remember to consult with a professional plumber to guarantee a successful and hassle-free installation process.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-1511329859.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  19th  September 2023', 1),
(155, '0', 'The difference between a circuit breaker and a fuse and the essential facts about them', 'The-difference-between-a-circuit-breaker-and-a-fuse-and-the-essential-facts-about-them', 'electrical', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f6ac9caf-09ca-49d0-89b4-8c95d7a74a55\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"09a88119-86c0-4e4a-8e3f-f4c955699388\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Fuse and circuit breakers are essential components in electrical systems that help protect against overcurrents and prevent potential hazards. While they serve similar purposes, there are some key differences between the two.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"92938ca8-e1c6-4862-8753-02133b1bc3fd\"><strong> </strong><span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-danger-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-danger-default/50 hover:bg-bg-danger-light-default\" data-issueid=\"528cb8a9-0f9b-4240-902c-cdd1115c11f0\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text fuse\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:A fuse\"><strong>fuse</strong></span> is a safety device that consists of a metal wire or strip that melts when exposed to excessive current. It is designed to break the circuit and interrupt <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"f83e1853-f33d-4839-bb3f-0310b3b95f6d\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text the flow of electricity in\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">the flow of electricity in</span> the event of a short circuit or overload. Fuses are available in different sizes and ratings, and they need to be replaced once they <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"fb5cb0a8-b472-4a6e-bb35-b7ed8a7f0236\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text have blown.\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">have blown.</span></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3d245071-b76e-4fc5-9516-bd0bc5d3db32\">On the other hand, </p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a2ee4144-5d33-4851-93e1-76eb04c00322\"><strong>a circuit breaker </strong>is an automatic switch that can be reset after it trips due to an overcurrent. It comprises a bi-metallic strip or an electromagnet that gets activated when the current exceeds a certain threshold. Once tripped, the circuit breaker isolates the faulty circuit, preventing further damage. Unlike fuses, circuit breakers do not need to be replaced but can simply be reset. This make circuit breaker more advantagous than fuses.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"93a4fb83-e732-44d5-8bb2-2cc2a2d962ec\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"09a88119-86c0-4e4a-8e3f-f4c955699388\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"><u class=\"underline\" style=\"background-color: rgb(231, 99, 99);\">One advantage of circuit breakers over fuses is their ability to handle short circuits and overloads without needing replacement.</u> Fuses, on the other hand, need to be replaced each time they blow. Additionally, circuit breakers provide better protection against electrical fires as they can quickly disconnect the power supply in case of a fault.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"517a9782-ea49-4310-803e-35cff07d4ac9\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"09a88119-86c0-4e4a-8e3f-f4c955699388\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">When it comes to selecting the right protection for your electrical system, there are a few factors to consider. The type and size of the circuit, the maximum current it can handle, and the specific requirements of the application all play a role in determining whether a fuse or a circuit breaker is the better choice.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"59e2908b-1712-49b1-b2bd-b92aaa7b4086\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"09a88119-86c0-4e4a-8e3f-f4c955699388\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In summary, fuses and circuit breakers are vital components in electrical systems that protect against overcurrents. While fuses require replacement after they blow, circuit breakers can be reset. When deciding between the two, it is important to consider the specific requirements and capabilities of the electrical system in question.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5283f23b-a88e-49f4-ac87-842ff8ef09b0\"></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"2e16e0f9-3422-434d-b299-8c6f7887477d\">Remember to follow my page for more engineering contents.</p>', 'iStock-1445374494.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  20th  September 2023', 1),
(156, '0', 'Gambia secure ticket to Cote d’Ivoire in dramatic fashion', 'Gambia-secure-ticket-to-Cote-d-Ivoire-in-dramatic-fashion', 'sports', '<p>&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>A dramatic turn of events at the Grand Stade de Marrakech, Morocco saw Gambia secure a dramatic qualification to the TotalEnergies CAF Africa Cup of Nations, Cote d’Ivoire 2023 following their 2-2 draw with Congo on Sunday night.</p><p><br></p><p>Needing just a point to secure their place in next year’s continental showpiece, the Scorpions had to come back from two goals down to salvage a draw and go through to their second TotalEnergies AFCON in history.</p><p><br></p><p>With Mali having already wrapped up their qualifiers campaign, it was left to the two sides to determine who would be the second team from Group G to make it through.</p><p><br></p><p>Unexpectedly so, Congo found the opener in the 34th minute after a quick break in transition saw Prestige Mboungou send a delightful cross to the near post that found Gaius Makouta, who did well to shield the ball from his marker and toe-poke the ball into the net.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>The goal seemed to put the Gambian defense in disarray as they struggled to keep possession from the onrushing Congolese attack.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>With just minutes to the break, Congo doubled their lead to the disbelief of Gambia when their skipper, Omar Colley handled the ball in the penalty area for the referee to point to the spot kick, as Silvere M’boussy stepped up to extend the lead.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Coming back from the break, the Scorpions tried to get back into the game with most of their attacks being orchestrated by the trio of Ebrima Colley, Assan Ceesay and Musa Barrow.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Beni Makouana could have put the match beyond reach after a well-threaded ball saw the midfielder through on goal as he did well to go around the keeper, but his right footed strike came off the upright in the 54th minute.</p><p><br></p><p>Congo remained resolute for the better part of the second stanza, but their defense was eventually breached in the 79th minute when Yankuba Minteh pulled one back to instill hope in his side after an assist from substitute, Muhammed Badamosi.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>With time not on their side, a goal was just enough for the Scorpions to scrape through, and they did just that in the 90th minute thanks to Badamosi again who rose above his markers to head into the bottom corner from a Musa Barrow cross.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>The result sees Gambia secure a place in Cote d’Ivoire along with Mali, while Congo and South Sudan miss out.</p>', '1695223229219.jpg', '', '', 'Source ', '  20th  September 2023', 1),
