(158, '0', 'The body of a missing Nigerian journalist was found in a pit', 'The-body-of-a-missing-Nigerian-journalist-was-found-in-a-pit', 'general news', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"fa8d3af4-eeab-4514-9332-13802bcbff6b\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"593342bc-fe5c-4c23-b1af-ccffb5efab87\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Hamisu Danjibga, a veteran Nigerian radio journalist, has been found dead three days after he went missing in Zamfara state, north-west Nigeria.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8e9f4922-5984-4b80-bf56-2faed8e84ca5\"></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9561ab8d-3857-47f8-8119-8471283d62b6\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"d33e55d9-dd2b-4311-bcf8-c61f0dd82c5b\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">For many years, Danjibga reported extensively on the widespread insecurity in Zamfara state for Voice of Nigeria (VON).</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3471e41f-5186-42de-bfbb-b40da041e1ed\"></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"23506c42-40db-40e9-ad10-c7fe2e3db05c\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"82bd1924-0c38-4d69-a5f7-dcd0c66399f0\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Before his body was found in a pit behind his house, he was declared missing early Monday morning.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"dff7b152-e964-4806-b2f6-24fc39e93006\"></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"bb2e16d9-f2cc-4ae1-9dd1-b4e8bd9b2425\">The Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ) and other press organisations have condemned <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"f528e25f-7497-44ef-a6eb-11aec10d9406\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text the alleged killing of Danjibga.\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">the alleged killing of Danjibga.</span></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d4e6b7c6-645e-4c1d-b92d-32d3763488c6\">Zamfara state Governor Dauda Lawal has ordered security agencies to investigate the incident.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"40218b2b-5d4b-4162-8b4e-6b090e1c729f\">Fellow journalists said Danjibga’s broadcast voice gave him an edge over others during his decades-long <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"48a6b120-6f6d-4856-8f67-b18c6694a868\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text career as a reporter.\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">career as a reporter.</span></p>', 'Hamisu-Danjibga-2.jpg', '', '', 'Source: BBC', '  22nd  September 2023', 1),
(161, '0', '5 Habits That Slowly Kill You Without You Realizing It', '5-Habits-That-Slowly-Kill-You-Without-You-Realizing-It', 'health and fitness', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"1b5b9e8c-dd14-4ccb-aa94-d4352f764a17\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In our fast-paced and hectic lives, it\'s easy to overlook the impact of certain habits that can silently deteriorate our health over time. This article sheds light on five common habits that slowly kill us without us even realizing it. By becoming aware of these habits, we can make conscious choices to protect our well-being and lead a healthier life.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0e9c3df5-e922-49b8-a644-944e0a1db796\"><strong><mark class=\"wordtune-highlight pt-[2px] pb-[3px] text-inherit bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-color=\"primary-lighter\">1.</mark><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Sedentary Lifestyle:</wt-ignore></strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"049427fb-720b-45c7-a8c1-2fa990b490fb\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In today\'s digital age, many of us spend extended periods sitting at desks or on the couch, leading a sedentary lifestyle. Prolonged sitting has been linked to a range of health problems, including obesity, heart disease, and increased risk of certain cancers. Regular physical activity is crucial to maintaining a healthy body and mind. Incorporating exercise into our daily routine, even in small increments, such as taking short walks or stretching breaks, can help counteract the harmful effects of a sedentary lifestyle.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"92f7b887-f195-4f29-b3ad-543b8f30301b\"><strong>2. Poor Diet:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4916f84b-8dac-41de-8cc6-d194f31a5479\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Unhealthy eating habits can have long-term consequences on our health. Consuming excessive amounts of processed foods, sugary snacks, and beverages high in added sugars can lead to weight gain, diabetes, and heart disease. A diet lacking in essential nutrients, such as fruits, vegetables, and whole grains, can weaken our immune system, making us more susceptible to illnesses. By prioritizing a balanced diet, rich in nutritious foods, we can nourish our bodies and reduce the risk of chronic diseases.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"23f16434-f8e3-40ee-a8ae-31ea56fff6c8\"><strong>3. Inadequate Sleep:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a74d2b1a-3eb3-4bfe-8a90-b8144dc31cca\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In our busy lives, sleep often takes a backseat. However, inadequate sleep can have serious health implications. Chronic sleep deprivation has been linked to a higher risk of obesity, diabetes, cardiovascular diseases, and mental health issues. Establishing a regular sleep schedule and creating a sleep-friendly environment can help improve the quantity and quality of our sleep, promoting overall well-being.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e3ba3aec-c333-42a7-9aed-2b28c38ec4b5\"><strong>4. Excessive Stress:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5c4954bf-3b02-41e4-a829-57be351f506d\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">While stress is a natural part of life, excessive and chronic stress can wreak havoc on our health. It has been associated with a range of ailments, including high blood pressure, heart disease, depression, and anxiety. Finding healthy ways to manage stress, such as practicing relaxation techniques, engaging in hobbies, or seeking support from loved ones, can significantly improve our physical and mental well-being.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8b611e4a-204c-47e3-b431-34b133c7374a\"><strong>5. Smoking and Excessive Alcohol Consumption:</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f63954ab-b5ba-4ef8-8cb1-cdc108969aae\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Tobacco and alcohol are two habits that pose significant risks to our health. Smoking is a leading cause of preventable diseases, including various types of cancer, heart disease, and respiratory problems. Excessive alcohol consumption can damage the liver, increase the risk of liver disease, and contribute to other health issues, such as hypertension and certain cancers. Quitting smoking and moderating alcohol intake are crucial steps towards improving our long-term health outcomes.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b867507a-33d1-48f2-a5e9-2ce78e5fa858\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Conclusion:</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b71a25b8-4540-4484-8892-93cf81fc9d28\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"c5114840-f639-45a6-8728-6400e6b4c5cc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By recognizing these five habits that slowly kill us without our realization, we can make informed choices to protect our well-being. Incorporating regular physical activity, adopting a balanced diet, prioritizing adequate sleep, managing stress effectively, and avoiding smoking and excessive alcohol consumption are essential steps towards leading a healthier and more fulfilling life. Let us take charge of our habits and pave the way for a brighter and healthier future.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-826826798.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  22nd  September 2023', 1);
