e:undefined\">put you in danger,</span> such as traffic, fire, or falling masonry. Next, check the person. Do they need help? Tap their shoulder and shout, “Are you OK?”</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b69dbcfd-da7c-4f56-bb8d-5636f1f724c0\">If they are not responding, call 911 or ask a bystander to call 911 before performing CPR.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"cfe53122-04d7-49ab-9b83-8eeab027b4ce\"><strong>Step 2. Place the person on their back and open their airway</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"afee1f0a-6b0c-4ef1-b5d7-4c9b1fd3eeca\">Place the person carefully on their back and kneel beside their chest. Tilt their <wt-ignore uuid=\"9673bc14-147f-4a99-8b1a-5812ff042bda\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">heads</wt-ignore> back slightly by lifting their <wt-ignore uuid=\"07fa70f6-d3d4-44f3-b287-7bfe7175a4b8\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">chins.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"daa37b66-9981-4ded-bcba-d399c0618f4f\"><strong>Step 3. Check for breathing</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8140a308-d63d-4e68-bb5d-73d7c1a7622a\">Place your ear <wt-ignore uuid=\"fe616f3a-9674-4347-acd7-0c73fcbd9f99\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">next to the</wt-ignore> person’s mouth and listen <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"12059444-d396-4f24-aa48-9c6cf1d9b5e4\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text for no more than 10\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">for no more than 10</span> seconds. If you do not hear breathing, <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"3ff56b81-1773-4d4c-bb49-b21a398ad9a3\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text or you only\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">or you only</span> hear occasional gasps, begin CPR.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"c4436c43-b786-430b-83fa-fe2524a33cac\">If someone is unconscious but still breathing, do <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"011bc24e-f195-4a73-8f6e-07957ecf69a5\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text not perform CPR.\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">not perform CPR.</span></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"82383c15-c16a-421d-b62b-1b686dc16a36\"><strong>CPR steps</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"41a3fe27-6dbd-40ff-894c-f9bbb50bede3\">Use the following steps to perform CPR:</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d2b913d9-59c0-4571-ad7b-04e65420801d\"><strong>Step 4. Perform 30 chest compressions</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e3b49cf4-e289-4886-8123-1679113dfd24\"></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"0b741f97-2dce-4f8d-8190-012153e3e4ee\">Place one of your hands on top of the other and clasp them together. With the heel of the hands and straight elbows, push hard and fast in the center of the chest, slightly below the <wt-ignore uuid=\"e8ec8fbb-480f-41b5-9876-e643b005c100\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">nipsles.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5bff1fbe-ef2d-45d6-9b5e-78150f33552c\">Push at least 2 inches deep. Compress their chest at a rate <wt-ignore uuid=\"21e510c6-bf57-445a-94fc-f924251b743c\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">of at least</wt-ignore> 100 times per minute. Let the chest rise fully between compressions.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"cd2f563b-be5b-4d5a-9dbb-fd176247f0e5\"><strong>Step 5. Perform two rescue breaths</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"07dd37e1-3ee8-4b3b-98c9-82e2ad6181b7\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"da408889-ca8e-48d6-85a1-ee0c4ca6d6b7\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Make</wt-ignore> sure their mouth is <wt-ignore uuid=\"cfe7186e-e376-498c-881b-954d5fd17be4\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">clear. Tip</wt-ignore> their <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-danger-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-danger-default/50 hover:bg-bg-danger-light-default\" data-issueid=\"fc901509-a1fd-4094-8f0a-cbd6272b097a\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text head\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:heads\">head</span> back slightly and lift their chin. Pinch their nose shut, place your mouth fully over theirs, and blow to <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"bc8cfe1a-93c9-4a37-a8bb-a978751f74bb\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text make their chest rise.\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">make their chest rise.</span></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"a048a849-4d13-4895-8786-cf66d2d80ac6\">If their chest does not rise with the first breath, <wt-ignore uuid=\"d2910422-2ecc-44f6-9a3b-afcfd7f9fafc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">retract</wt-ignore> their head. If their chest still does not rise with a second breath, the person might be choking.</p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d0809b5f-8b02-440a-a49c-405576c46754\"><strong>Step 6. Repeat</strong></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"859207e7-eefb-44a8-9db6-47dd42ac4b72\">Repeat the cycle of 30 chest compressions and two rescue breaths until the person starts breathing or help arrives. If an AED arrives, <span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"5a4df721-5009-4cca-aaea-42ce757edbe4\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text carry on performing\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\">carry on performing</span> CPR until the machine is set up and ready to use.</p>', 'main-qimg-b6bb2ed3c5f0abb90078ad62b5a590f5.jpeg', '', '', 'source ', '  26th  September 2023', 1),
(203, '0', '5 Things You Can Do to Prevent Smelly Drains', '5-Things-You-Can-Do-to-Prevent-Smelly-Drains', 'plumbing', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"976738bd-d886-4964-9eea-c68b269b39d1\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"d2608c73-1f59-4adb-940f-33d08fb19148\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">5 Things You Can Do to Prevent Smelly Drains </wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"05762796-3abb-483e-9337-1475cc017da4\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"76c72564-1169-46dd-9baf-80fcaf6a2ab4\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Imagine</wt-ignore> having a smelly drain around you? <wt-ignore uuid=\"cd7167c1-36e4-4728-be8b-da69c099825d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">This causes so</wt-ignore> much <wt-ignore uuid=\"f3c68960-545c-47a7-b058-dc0b40c3d439\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">discomfort for</wt-ignore> you and the <wt-ignore uuid=\"07dbaa5f-8815-4046-8ca8-0a881bf376a2\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">people</wt-ignore> around you. <wt-ignore uuid=\"d3235cad-a2ba-479e-bf01-46613f9a4abe\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Whenever the weather gets</wt-ignore> hot, <wt-ignore uuid=\"a88efccc-c391-409e-9a33-63a38280ed55\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">instead</wt-ignore> of opening your windows you rather <wt-ignore uuid=\"7d1d72c8-f104-4bbc-b070-f091a229f1c8\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">close them just</wt-ignore> to <wt-ignore uuid=\"6a664e2c-92bf-4f99-9832-5f5eb38a45dc\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">prevent</wt-ignore> the bad smells from your <wt-ignore uuid=\"4efd9904-37e6-450d-8c49-c411cb40679d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">drain</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"8a2bdce9-03b1-4b3a-8aec-a6831c06a83c\">In this article <wt-ignore uuid=\"68f13d8f-0f31-4d6b-b2b1-2af2ca13d2d4\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">I am going to</wt-ignore> teach you how to prevent smelly <wt-ignore uuid=\"3eb1fc5d-e0e1-4e41-b10d-aa9d6dac4175\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">drains.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5e28f343-3956-4582-81f1-22588f81a4d3\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"01011553-8458-4601-bbbe-7a7527d03639\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Here</wt-ignore> are some ways to <wt-ignore uuid=\"c953c879-e8b5-4430-99fa-a62f951a6f30\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">prevent</wt-ignore> smelly <wt-ignore uuid=\"39c9cd72-e641-48cd-8492-310ecfb924f6\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">drains:</wt-ignore> </p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9039c66c-6a73-4a27-b68a-d5b0eedc0f04\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"009c90c4-e3bf-48a8-a6bc-c9bdaa3f5e9d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Do not forget to share this with anyone who disturbs your nose with smelly drains.</wt-ignore><wt-ignore uuid=\"a60e634f-6360-4e9e-ad87-1aaa895fefda\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> </wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"17ed7746-9795-49ce-a70e-6f6e3b63921b\"><strong>1. Regularly clean your drains:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"d2608c73-1f59-4adb-940f-33d08fb19148\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> One of the simplest and most effective ways to prevent smelly drains is to clean them regularly. Use a drain cleaner or a mixture of vinegar and baking soda to break down any buildup or residue that may be causing the odor. Pour the cleaner down the drain and let it sit for a few minutes before flushing it out with hot water.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ad2277a9-30d1-4d7a-b4d6-52c88bee2cae\"><strong>2. Avoid pouring grease down the drain:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"d2608c73-1f59-4adb-940f-33d08fb19148\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Grease and oil can quickly accumulate in your drains and lead to unpleasant smells. Instead of pouring grease down the drain, collect it in a container and dispose of it in the trash once it has solidified. This will not only help prevent smelly drains but also prevent clogs and blockages.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"2f78f5d4-8cca-40da-a157-f449993460a8\"><strong>3. Use a drain strainer:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"d2608c73-1f59-4adb-940f-33d08fb19148\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Install a drain strainer in your sinks and showers to catch hair, food particles, and other debris before they can go down the drain. This simple device can significantly reduce the amount of buildup in your drains and prevent foul odors from developing.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5fe69556-e9b1-46f5-86e5-25904df487bb\"><strong>4. Flush your drains with boiling water:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"d2608c73-1f59-4adb-940f-33d08fb19148\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Once a week, pour boiling water down your drains to help flush away any accumulated residue or bacteria. Boiling water can help dissolve greasy substances and kill odor-causing bacteria, keeping your drains fresh and odor-free.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"41b8f164-2ae2-4ff7-b2bc-4717c42563b4\"><strong>5. Maintain proper ventilation:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"d2608c73-1f59-4adb-940f-33d08fb19148\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Proper ventilation is crucial in preventing smelly drains. Make sure that your bathroom and kitchen are well-ventilated to allow moisture to escape. Moisture buildup can lead to mold and mildew growth, which can contribute to foul smells. Open windows, use exhaust fans, or consider installing a dehumidifier to keep the air circulating and prevent stagnant odors.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"7a8b89fa-fb2b-4273-9f4f-b4cf28380d46\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"d2608c73-1f59-4adb-940f-33d08fb19148\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">By following these simple tips, you can effectively prevent smelly drains and maintain a fresh, clean environment in your home. Regular cleaning, proper disposal of grease, using drain strainers, flushing with boiling water, and ensuring proper ventilation will help keep your drains odor-free and ensure a pleasant living space.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-906865804.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  26th  September 2023', 1);
