(224, '0', 'What are the behaviors of a confident person?', 'What-are-the-behaviors-of-a-confident-person-', 'lifestyle', '<li data-pm-slice=\"2 2 []\"><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d253e34a-021e-4c75-91ab-f7a3f7340b27\" style=\"text-align: left; \"><strong>Don’t say ‘I think’ or ‘I’m not sure’ </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"abcdd2b6-3d32-4367-bf28-a83d4015f643\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">A confident person speaks clearly and confidently, without hesitating. They are not afraid to take risks and challenge themselves, and they make decisions based on logic and reason. They are also not afraid to stand up for what they believe in.</wt-ignore></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f7d268c6-ba53-4ebc-afd0-e6e4676dfad1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Speak slowly and clearly. </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"4cb2d165-c0c3-4e3c-ba92-a82eb19bf51b\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Avoid using fillers such as \'umm\' or \'like\'. Speak with a firm tone of voice and maintain eye contact with the other person. Maintain a steady pace and use clear and concise language.</wt-ignore></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"668dad52-94d7-46fc-a33a-df9bff7d919b\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Allow silences. </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"1ff9660f-9782-4604-95ec-4b4fcc262d7d\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Relax and remain calm. Listen to the other person and respond appropriately. Wait for the other person to finish speaking before you respond.</wt-ignore></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ad69ec7f-ac1c-4eca-80e8-d8b2ff16dfaa\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Don’t hide your hands by stuffing them in your pockets or folding your arms. Use them. </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"87f61936-a41f-4066-9dc2-49a0d50368bd\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Relax your body and make eye contact. Show empathy and be interested in what the other person has to say. Keep an open posture and smile.</wt-ignore></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"b1e92d7c-30f2-484d-8c68-bef965bccbbf\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Build your assertiveness with “I” statements. </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cdb7059-0c7e-4d8e-b283-f13f9e7622ec\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Use active listening techniques, such as repeating back what the other person said to show you are listening. Ask questions to clarify points, and don\'t be afraid to challenge ideas. Give constructive feedback.</wt-ignore></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"12ea5bf8-2c83-4916-9957-e48feb09db51\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Instead of asking yourself, “What’s the worst that can happen?” try asking, “What’s the best that can happen?”</strong></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9cbe0c2a-aacc-42b3-bfe4-1efb133dd3eb\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Combat fright by visualizing success. </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"5cf6f3f5-eb93-41e3-bc06-e1064ef3a500\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">This can shift your mindset and help you focus on what is possible instead of what could go wrong. By picturing yourself succeeding, you are more likely to feel confident and motivated to take the necessary steps to achieve your goals.</wt-ignore></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d18ca5c9-c4cd-46be-a46c-c46852f8291e\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Pause more during conversations. </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"53640f8d-4611-49ef-8b8c-7a8b47cf48d1\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">This can help you think more clearly and better understand the other person\'s point of view. It also gives you a chance to choose a better response or outcome. Finally, it can help you to stay calm and focused in challenging situations.</wt-ignore></p></li><li><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"77f7cde5-8100-4b67-b416-60f141dd4b20\" style=\"text-align: left; \"><strong>People tend to view speakers </strong><span class=\"issue-underline underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4 transition decoration-border-brand-default [.long-form-editing-active_&amp;]:decoration-border-brand-default/50 hover:bg-bg-brand-light-default\" data-issueid=\"5eb8cf09-e264-4066-ad9f-b746234c5975\" aria-label=\"open issue for the following text with lower speaking voices\" data-testid=\"issue-underline:undefined\"><strong>with lower speaking voices</strong></span><strong> as having more authority and confidence. </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"e62c4e1e-8004-4a17-8042-de7654991f37\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Taking pauses can also help you to find the right words to express your thoughts more clearly. Additionally, it can help you to come across as more sincere and genuine in your conversations.</wt-ignore></p></li>', 'Picture10.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  4th  October 2023', 1),
