(232, '0', 'How to Recognize a True Friend: 8 Signs', 'How-to-Recognize-a-True-Friend-8-Signs', 'Dating and Relationship', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"e21f0482-9018-4da2-ae30-37a3d6062724\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><br></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"911a3076-4017-4dc9-ab75-2317d05b1ef5\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Having true friends in life is invaluable. They are the ones who stand by us through thick and thin, offering support, understanding, and loyalty. But how can we differentiate between true friends and mere acquaintances? Here are eight signs to help you recognize a true friend.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"3a896fd6-75a6-4937-a2e4-d734396ad17e\"><strong>1. Trustworthiness:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> A true friend is someone you can confide in without fear of judgment or betrayal. They keep your secrets safe and honor their commitments.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"d5ef1a10-05f8-4da7-b236-82da8be99236\"><strong>2. Reliability:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> True friends are dependable. They are there for you when you need them, offering a helping hand or a listening ear. They follow through on their promises and are consistent in their actions.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"c890bf07-fbcc-4c92-83c6-8d0839608d3c\"><strong>3. Acceptance:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> A true friend accepts you for who you are, flaws and all. They embrace your imperfections and love you unconditionally, without trying to change or mold you into someone else.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"bab4c8ff-5462-462e-8b07-41516d0535f3\"><strong>4. Empathy:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> True friends genuinely care about your feelings and emotions. They actively listen, show empathy, and provide support during difficult times. They understand your perspective and provide comfort without judgment.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"c351f2f6-9b20-4d4e-a29f-ec83f17a0cad\"><strong>5. Loyalty:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> True friends are fiercely loyal. They have your back and stand up for you, even when others may turn away. They defend your reputation, support your dreams, and celebrate your successes.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"36130d11-e546-4c6c-bd40-e7a101ec1384\"><strong>6. Honesty:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> True friends are honest with you, even when it\'s difficult. They offer constructive criticism when needed and are not afraid to speak their mind. Their honesty comes from a place of genuine concern and a desire to see you grow.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"982ab29c-511e-474a-af78-47b8e55f9877\"><strong>7. Mutual Respect:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> True friends treat you with respect and expect the same in return. They value your opinions, boundaries, and personal space. They recognize your worth and treat you as an equal.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"6afdba24-2d61-4e66-a668-6e5f4a146818\"><strong>8. Time and Effort:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> True friends invest time and effort into the relationship. They make an effort to stay in touch, spend quality time together, and nurture the connection. They prioritize your friendship and make it a priority in their lives.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"f06b3516-c497-46ad-92bb-2010513d85b9\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"f1caf274-31fc-45f4-971e-013e4422803a\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In conclusion, recognizing a true friend involves looking for signs of trustworthiness, reliability, acceptance, empathy, loyalty, honesty, mutual respect, and the investment of time and effort. True friends are rare gems that enrich our lives, and by understanding these signs, we can cultivate and cherish these precious relationships.</wt-ignore></p>', 'iStock-1413936380.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  5th  October 2023', 1),
(233, '0', '10 Shocking Facts About Romantic Love No One Knows', '10-Shocking-Facts-About-Romantic-Love-No-One-Knows', 'Dating and Relationship', '<p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"5af0984a-aa2c-47bc-abd6-4cc4f6b63d62\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><strong>1. Love at first sight is not just a cliché:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> While it may seem like a fairytale, research suggests that initial attraction can occur within seconds of meeting someone. The brain releases a surge of chemicals, leading to feelings of infatuation and intense attraction.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"38965a38-a8ab-487a-bcee-6d55adcd7f56\"><strong>2. Love can be addictive: </strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">Similar to drugs, romantic love can activate the brain\'s reward system, releasing dopamine and creating a sense of euphoria. This can lead to obsessive thoughts and behaviors, as individuals become addicted to the feeling of being in love.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"ecb97f90-03f8-4d35-9624-260076b06b8e\"><strong>3. Love can make you blind:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> When we are in love, we tend to idealize our partners and overlook their flaws. This phenomenon, known as \"rose-colored glasses,\" can prevent us from seeing red flags or warning signs in the relationship.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"db78b3d1-8e03-48ed-99c0-b0823a763aaa\"><strong>4. Love can affect your physical health:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Being in a loving relationship has been linked to numerous health benefits, such as lower blood pressure, reduced stress levels, and a stronger immune system. On the other hand, heartbreak and unrequited love can have detrimental effects on both mental and physical well-being.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"aafde510-4a37-4472-b955-5ce5997a029e\"><strong>5. Love can change your brain:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Studies have shown that being in love can alter the brain\'s structure and chemistry. Certain areas of the brain associated with reward, bonding, and empathy become more active, while the amygdala, responsible for fear and aggression, becomes less active.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"50a1ff4d-b248-4eef-b9a4-efe5e2343697\"><strong>6. Love can be influenced by scent:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Pheromones, chemical signals released by the body, can play a role in attraction and mate selection. Research suggests that we are subconsciously attracted to individuals with a different immune system, which can be detected through scent.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"4e522624-9ee9-4fd3-aae0-a87c28a4d508\"><strong>7. Love can be contagious:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Just like a yawn, love can be contagious. Being around happy and loving couples can increase the likelihood of experiencing romantic feelings. This is known as the \"social contagion\" of love.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"6fbd9459-9552-459b-959a-1280580ce22a\"><strong>8. Love can be a source of pain:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> The same brain areas that are activated when we experience physical pain can also be activated when we experience emotional pain from a breakup or rejection. This explains why heartbreak can be so physically and emotionally painful.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"908688ca-79ad-40e1-bdca-6ee6d7428633\"><strong>9. Love can be influenced by timing:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Timing plays a crucial role in romantic love. Research suggests that individuals are more likely to fall in love when they are in a positive emotional state, such as after a personal achievement or during a vacation.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"9f3cc3c4-6c88-4894-926e-ef9108534b65\"><strong>10. Love can be everlasting:</strong><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\"> Contrary to popular belief, the \"honeymoon phase\" doesn\'t necessarily have to fade. With effort, communication, and commitment, couples can maintain the passionate and intense feelings associated with romantic love throughout their relationship.</wt-ignore></p><p data-private=\"redact\" class=\"pb-2\" data-wt-guid=\"2dec8ab6-41ec-475d-8c82-b222dd97929d\"><wt-ignore uuid=\"28491ddd-e34b-4892-a721-9d288fdaca11\" source=\"wt-feature-result\">In conclusion, romantic love is a complex and fascinating phenomenon that can have profound effects on our emotions, behaviors, and well-being. These shocking facts shed light on the intricacies of love, challenging common misconceptions and highlighting the power it holds over us.</wt-ignore></p>', 'istockphoto-1398995192-2048x2048.jpg', '', '', 'source ', '  5th  October 2023', 1),
